article.headline: UAB 84, Tulsa 54
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Carldell "Squeaky" Johnson had 13 points, five assists, and four steals to lead UAB to an 84-54 victory over Tulsa on Wednesday night. UAB (11-3, 1-0 Conference USA) forced a school-record 39 turnovers and finished with 21 steals. Lawrence Kinnard scored 10 points for the Blazers. Anthony Price had 14 points and seven rebounds to lead Tulsa (5-9, 0-1). The Golden Hurricane outrebounded UAB 44-22, but UAB's 39-8 advantage in turnovers made the difference. It was the second game for the Blazers without their No. 2 scorer, Demario Eddins, who is out for the season with a torn Achilles tendon. UAB started off slowly and fell behind 9-4, but a jump shot by Kinnard garnered a 12-11 lead and the Blazers never looked back. An 18-0 run late in the first half helped UAB to a 47-23 halftime lead. The Blazers lead by as many as 38 points in the second half.
